1
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,780
♪Trap my frame♪

2
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:20,060
♪Plagues demand I bow in shame♪

3
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Snare my soul♪

4
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:27,100
♪Rules command I swallow my pride♪

5
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:30,620
♪Mock my way♪

6
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,060
♪Chained me where I must stay♪

7
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,780
♪Taught me to kneel, not to speak♪

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:41,220
♪And to let my life pass by in silence♪

9
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
♪But I heard the wind♪

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,900
♪From the sea and the sky♪

11
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:47,660
♪It said don't bend♪

12
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,820
♪Bow your head, and your chains begin♪

13
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,380
♪You are the wave♪

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
♪And the wind that won't behave♪

15
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,340
♪How could you be chained?♪

16
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,740
♪Untamed, uncaged, unclaimed♪

17
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:00,540
♪You're the blade in my gaze♪

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,420
♪This world will leave you no space♪

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,220
♪Then pierce it with your blaze♪

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,100
♪My silent grind♪

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,060
♪My aching pain♪

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:10,300
♪Will one day turn...♪

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:14,620
♪I am who I am♪

24
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,140
♪My greatest ambition♪

25
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,300
♪If the world can't contain me♪

26
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:24,940
♪Then I'll break through it♪

27
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,940
♪Become who I am♪

28
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,260
[Wild Ambition Bloom]

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,980
[Adapted from Stone and Water's novel,
The Uncaged Flame]

30
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 37]

31
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:33,900
You...

32
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,620
should go talk to Mr. Xia.

33
00:01:37,070 --> 00:01:38,100
He knows more than I do.

34
00:01:38,590 --> 00:01:39,460
Mr. Xia?

35
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,930
All he cares about

36
00:01:42,230 --> 00:01:43,460
is profit.

37
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:44,690
Justice and truth don't even register.

38
00:01:45,510 --> 00:01:47,180
But you're different.

39
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:49,620
He brought me into the business.

40
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,850
How could I be any different?

41
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,130
Deep down,

42
00:01:53,870 --> 00:01:55,210
you're nothing like him.

43
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,690
Xia Yuan

44
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:03,740
is my boss,

45
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:05,980
my mentor,

46
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:07,820
and the one I owe everything to.

47
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:12,100
I would never betray him.

48
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,290
But the Mr. Gao I know

49
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:18,730
would never go against his conscience.

50
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:22,500
Mr. Gao,

51
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,340
when I began managing an apothecary,

52
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:27,730
I met you.

53
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:30,010
Even though we didn't meet often,

54
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,450
your humility and integrity

55
00:02:32,710 --> 00:02:34,340
have always earned my deepest respect.

56
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:37,060
It made me swear to myself

57
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,730
I'd manage my business just as you did,

58
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,290
with honesty

59
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:43,130
and

60
00:02:43,910 --> 00:02:44,940
integrity.

61
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,500
So I'm here waiting for you,

62
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:51,130
just to ask you one question.

63
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:54,100
Did my mother really sell
the Miracle Pill formula

64
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,610
to Mr. Xia?

65
00:02:57,590 --> 00:02:58,450
Mr. Gao.

66
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:03,570
Miss Chu,

67
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,780
I am no longer

68
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:10,380
the same person I used to be.

69
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:13,260
I'll take my leave.

70
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:22,450
Dig in.

71
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,100
Come on.

72
00:04:01,190 --> 00:04:01,890
Shaozhong.

73
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,170
Shaohua?

74
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:11,850
You're back.

75
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:13,290
Shaozhong,

76
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:14,500
how are you holding up?

77
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,170
I'm fine.

78
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:17,700
Really.

79
00:04:18,390 --> 00:04:19,170
Where's Bao?

80
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:20,660
He's working as an apprentice

81
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,700
and comes back once a week.

82
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,700
What about Song Ping?

83
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:26,220
She's at Mr. Wang's.

84
00:04:27,630 --> 00:04:28,900
Why are you back?

85
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:32,340
Things are getting worse in North China.

86
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,290
I want to take you all to Shanghai.

87
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:35,980
Also,

88
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:38,340
I want to ask you something important.

89
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,290
That's not true.

90
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,540
Are you sure?

91
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,170
Of course.

92
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,460
Mr. Yi talked to me
a few times back then,

93
00:04:45,870 --> 00:04:47,340
but only about buying
Chichun Apothecary.

94
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,250
He never once mentioned
the Miracle Pill.

95
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,580
And

96
00:04:51,190 --> 00:04:52,900
even if it really had been sold,

97
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:55,540
Mother and Zhou Yan would've told me.

98
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:58,490
Is there a chance

99
00:04:58,830 --> 00:05:00,020
they sold it

100
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,580
but didn't dare tell you?

101
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:02,460
No.

102
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,780
I've seen the contract.

103
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:07,340
It only mentioned the signboard.

104
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,170
Miracle Pill wasn't in it at all.

105
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,810
And it was only sold
for 160 silver dollars,

106
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:14,580
not 180.

107
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,460
Where is that contract now?

108
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,700
Can you still find it?

109
00:05:21,390 --> 00:05:23,290
That was over 20 years ago.

110
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:24,730
Where would I even find it now?

111
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:27,810
Shaozhong,
maybe we should try looking again.

112
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,900
It's definitely gone.

113
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,100
Shaozhong,

114
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,460
are any of Mother's fingerprints
still in the house?

115
00:05:56,510 --> 00:05:57,100
No.

116
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:58,540
What about Zhou Yan's?

117
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,050
None either.

118
00:06:05,630 --> 00:06:06,930
If it's truly nowhere to be found,

119
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:08,290
I'll return to Shanghai with you.

120
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,700
If Xia Yuan insists on
seizing the Miracle Pill,

121
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,250
I'll fight him to the very end.

122
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:14,810
At worst, we'll both go down.

123
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:16,900
Shaozhong, don't worry.

124
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:18,050
Even if we can't find it,

125
00:06:18,070 --> 00:06:19,410
we still have other ways.

126
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:21,980
What other ways?

127
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:25,020
Isn't this contract in triplicate?

128
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,540
We have one.

129
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,490
Xia Yuan does too.

130
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:29,660
So does Anke Hall.

131
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:33,020
Since the Qizhou Medicine Market
shut down,

132
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:34,370
Anke Hall closed with it.

133
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:36,490
But we can still track down
the one in charge, right?

134
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,460
If we can find Lei Yuting,

135
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:40,170
we still have a chance.

136
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:44,340
Lei Yuting?

137
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,460
He died in 1930.

138
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,250
How could this be?

139
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,220
Sir,

140
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:53,100
are there old contracts

141
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:53,850
from Anke Hall here?

142
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:55,490
They're all piled up inside.

143
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,490
[Anke Hall]
Can we go in and take a look?

144
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,290
Sir, please help us.

145
00:07:07,830 --> 00:07:08,540
Come with me.

146
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,660
Come on, they're all in here.

147
00:07:19,830 --> 00:07:20,340
Okay.

148
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,050
Is this the right key?

149
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,100
Don't get it wrong.

150
00:07:38,630 --> 00:07:39,610
It can't be wrong.

151
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:42,170
Last month, I used this key

152
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:43,290
to open this lock.

153
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:47,730
It's open.

154
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:48,460
Okay.

155
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,930
Go ahead and check for yourselves.

156
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:58,930
Okay.

157
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:01,250
No one came for over a decade.

158
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,460
Then there were two visits this month.

159
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,460
How strange.

160
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,460
Shaozhong, how about this?

161
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:11,930
You look over there,

162
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:12,810
and I'll look here.

163
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,140
Let's start from 1916.

164
00:08:15,310 --> 00:08:15,850
Okay.

165
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,700
About my height.

166
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,850
Big eyes. Very thin.

167
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,530
You mean that woman from the North?

168
00:08:33,550 --> 00:08:34,100
Zhou, right?

169
00:08:34,270 --> 00:08:34,730
Yes.

170
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:37,100
Do you know where she is now?

171
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:48,130
She's dead.

172
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:09,580
The year of 1917.

173
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:10,490
Shaohua.

174
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,100
Is this it?

175
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:13,530
Let me see.

176
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:16,440
[Land Deed. Year 1916]

177
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,060
Let's go over there.

178
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:19,700
- Come on.
- Okay.

179
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:25,770
Here.

180
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:39,890
Shaozhong.

181
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,420
This is it.

182
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,060
The situation

183
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,180
is not looking good for Shaohua.

184
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:57,820
We need to blur the facts.

185
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,370
Just find a few random fingerprints

186
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:02,580
and claim they belong to her mother
and Zhou Yan.

187
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,490
The prints can't be confirmed,

188
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,300
and the judge won't know either.

189
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:08,300
No need, Wen.

190
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,820
Shaohua found key evidence in Qizhou,

191
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,370
enough to prove that Xia Yuan's contract

192
00:10:13,630 --> 00:10:14,300
is a forgery.

193
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:17,850
That's great.

194
00:10:20,180 --> 00:10:20,940
Mr. Xia.

195
00:10:20,940 --> 00:10:23,540
[Shanghai Public Court]

196
00:10:26,380 --> 00:10:27,220
Miss Chu,

197
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:30,260
you can still change your mind.

198
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:31,420
Mr. Xia.

199
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:34,260
Truth doesn't change,

200
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:35,860
and lies won't hold up.

201
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:39,500
Once we're in court,

202
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,180
the Miracle Pill's as good as mine.

203
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:02,100
Your Honor,

204
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:06,300
based on the witnesses, testimonies,
and evidence presented,

205
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,900
[Plaintiff]
we request a ruling

206
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,140
that Shaohua Pharmaceuticals

207
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:13,890
[Defendant]
return the Miracle Pill formula

208
00:11:13,890 --> 00:11:14,980
to Shouyuan Apothecary.

209
00:11:15,660 --> 00:11:17,860
All prior profits

210
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:19,940
from its sale

211
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:22,220
should also be returned.

212
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:25,940
Defense Lawyer,

213
00:11:26,540 --> 00:11:29,100
do you have any arguments to present

214
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,060
regarding the plaintiff's
evidence and claims?

215
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:34,020
Your Honor,

216
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:36,740
the sales contract submitted
by the plaintiff

217
00:11:37,060 --> 00:11:37,820
is forged.

218
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:40,060
You need evidence to support that.

219
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:41,340
Defense Lawyer,

220
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:44,460
do you have any evidence
to support your statement?

221
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:45,900
Your Honor,

222
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:48,980
the submitted contract states:

223
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:50,100
"Empty words prove nothing.

224
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:51,620
This sales contract is the evidence,

225
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:52,820
issued in triplicate.

226
00:11:53,380 --> 00:11:55,260
One copy each is held by the signatory,

227
00:11:55,260 --> 00:11:56,060
the contract holder, and Anke Hall."

228
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:58,540
While the signatory's copy
is no longer available,

229
00:11:58,740 --> 00:12:02,020
we have located

230
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:03,500
the original contract

231
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:04,900
in the Qizhou Anke Hall archives.

232
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:10,340
Please note

233
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:12,940
that while the two contracts
are very similar,

234
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:15,940
the copy archived by Anke Hall

235
00:12:16,580 --> 00:12:18,740
does not contain the phrase

236
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:19,420
"Miracle Pill formula."

237
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:22,500
Since the relevant parties
are either missing

238
00:12:22,540 --> 00:12:23,580
or have passed away,

239
00:12:24,060 --> 00:12:24,980
comparatively,

240
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,940
the copy archived by Anke Hall

241
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:28,580
is more credible.

242
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:41,460
Your Honor,

243
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:43,940
we request a thorough review

244
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,420
of the defendant's evidence.

245
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:10,540
Your Honor,

246
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:12,980
it's the defendant's contract

247
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:14,740
that's forged.

248
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:16,620
You need evidence to support that.

249
00:13:17,220 --> 00:13:21,140
The signatures and fingerprints
of Xia Yuan and Gao Qianyi

250
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:23,300
are not theirs at all.

251
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,060
If you keep talking nonsense,

252
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:25,940
I swear I'll knock you out.

253
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:27,900
Of the six people who left fingerprints,

254
00:13:28,220 --> 00:13:29,620
three have passed away,

255
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:30,740
and one is missing.

256
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:36,900
But Xia Yuan and Gao Qianyi
are still alive,

257
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:39,420
and present in this courtroom.

258
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:41,180
We request

259
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:43,900
immediate fingerprint verification.

260
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,140
Sure, do it.

261
00:13:45,460 --> 00:13:46,220
We'll see who's bluffing.

262
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,380
No one came for over a decade.

263
00:13:48,380 --> 00:13:49,700
Then there were two visits this month.

264
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,660
How strange.

265
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:52,820
Miss Chu, do you agree
to the on-site identification?

266
00:13:56,020 --> 00:13:56,780
No need.

267
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:57,780
Why?

268
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:02,380
We've been tricked.

269
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:03,900
What do you mean?

270
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:05,740
The contract we brought back

271
00:14:06,540 --> 00:14:08,180
from Anke Hall

272
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,180
is a forgery.

273
00:14:11,820 --> 00:14:12,940
How is that possible?

274
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:15,180
Looks like Xia Yuan

275
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,860
placed a fake contract

276
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:19,220
in the archives,

277
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:23,740
hoping we'd fall for it.

278
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:29,540
Your Honor,

279
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:31,540
we do not agree
to the on-site identification.

280
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:33,260
Feeling guilty, are you?

281
00:14:33,660 --> 00:14:35,700
Due to unforeseen circumstances,

282
00:14:35,940 --> 00:14:37,740
we request a brief recess.

283
00:14:38,140 --> 00:14:38,860
That won't do,

284
00:14:39,540 --> 00:14:42,060
unless you acknowledge
the evidence was forged.

285
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,180
Order.

286
00:14:45,060 --> 00:14:46,980
Witness Gao Qianyi,
please take the stand.

287
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:08,820
Witness,

288
00:15:09,540 --> 00:15:10,820
please state your identity.

289
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:13,340
My name is Gao Qianyi,

290
00:15:13,820 --> 00:15:16,780
and I am the second shopkeeper
of Shouyuan Apothecary.

291
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,460
Present the evidence.

292
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:26,620
Take his fingerprints.

293
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:47,620
Your Honor,

294
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:49,820
even without collecting fingerprints,

295
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:51,620
we can still determine

296
00:15:51,860 --> 00:15:54,020
the contract submitted by Miss Chu

297
00:15:54,420 --> 00:15:55,340
is evidently forged.

298
00:15:55,980 --> 00:15:59,060
There's a whorl fingerprint
on the contract,

299
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:03,060
but all my fingers have loop patterns.

300
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:07,100
Mr. Xia's contract

301
00:16:07,660 --> 00:16:08,940
does contain my fingerprint.

302
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:13,500
But

303
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,580
his copy

304
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:18,420
is also fake.

305
00:16:19,660 --> 00:16:21,100
I stamped it myself

306
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:25,060
twenty days ago.

307
00:16:25,780 --> 00:16:28,300
And I remember

308
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:29,980
that the contract back then

309
00:16:30,220 --> 00:16:32,860
didn't mention the Miracle Pill at all.

310
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:35,780
Gao Qianyi, you ungrateful wretch!

311
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:36,740
Save it for later.

312
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,620
Mr. Gao, thank you.

313
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:01,620
I truly didn't expect

314
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:03,900
that you would come to my defense

315
00:17:04,380 --> 00:17:06,860
at the most crucial moment.

316
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:10,220
Actually,

317
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:12,740
Xia Yuan's tactics
in acquiring Chichun Apothecary

318
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:14,660
were nothing short of despicable.

319
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:18,700
If he were to seize the Miracle Pill
in the same ruthless way,

320
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:21,020
that would be downright unjust.

321
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:22,980
I couldn't just stand by,

322
00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:24,340
so I chose to speak out.

323
00:17:25,780 --> 00:17:29,340
When my family sold
Chichun Apothecary to Xia Yuan,

324
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:31,540
it was out of desperation,

325
00:17:32,460 --> 00:17:33,980
but the decision was still our own.

326
00:17:36,580 --> 00:17:38,140
Miss Chu, as you know,

327
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,620
back then, Shouyuan Apothecary

328
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:41,780
dealt exclusively
in wholesale raw medicinal materials.

329
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:43,500
Back in 1916,

330
00:17:43,980 --> 00:17:46,620
Xia Yuan sought to enter
the prepared medicine market,

331
00:17:47,980 --> 00:17:49,300
so he set his sights on acquiring

332
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,740
the century-old Chichun Apothecary.

333
00:17:52,060 --> 00:17:54,460
But your brother flat-out refused.

334
00:17:56,180 --> 00:17:57,460
At the same time,

335
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:00,260
the Guandong and Qizhou Trade Guilds

336
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:03,740
were locked in a years-long struggle

337
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,580
to control pricing power
in the Qizhou Medicine Market

338
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:07,100
with neither side
gaining the upper hand.

339
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:09,940
So Xia Yuan devised a plan

340
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,980
that served both his ambitions.

341
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:15,500
He first had Yi Dajin use fake Huangqi

342
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:17,820
to replace the genuine stock
held by the Guandong Trade Guild,

343
00:18:18,060 --> 00:18:21,740
damaging their reputation and business
in the process.

344
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,140
Then he arranged for someone

345
00:18:23,420 --> 00:18:25,260
to resell that original batch of Huangqi

346
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:26,740
to your brother.

347
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:29,540
That was quicker than expected.

348
00:18:29,540 --> 00:18:32,820
Later, under the guise
of assisting the investigation,

349
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:35,460
he caught your brother in the act

350
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:38,500
and handed him over to Mr. Yang
to deal with.

351
00:18:38,580 --> 00:18:41,260
That gave him leverage over Mr. Yang.

352
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:42,860
Meanwhile, your brother,

353
00:18:43,340 --> 00:18:45,340
in order to purchase
all the genuine Huangqi,

354
00:18:45,620 --> 00:18:46,980
took on loan shark debt,

355
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:51,140
which ultimately forced your family

356
00:18:51,660 --> 00:18:54,380
to hand over Chichun Apothecary to him.

357
00:18:56,180 --> 00:18:56,900
So...

358
00:18:58,660 --> 00:19:01,420
it was Xia Yuan all along.

359
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:02,220
Precisely.

360
00:19:03,260 --> 00:19:06,020
However, there was
an interesting side story to this.

361
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:07,620
Yi Dajin

362
00:19:07,620 --> 00:19:09,460
had originally planned for Wu

363
00:19:09,780 --> 00:19:12,220
to expose the Guandong Trade Guild
for selling fake Huangqi.

364
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:13,860
But when it was time for him to testify,

365
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:15,860
he vanished.

366
00:19:15,980 --> 00:19:18,660
In the end, it was you
who uncovered the fake Huangqi

367
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:19,900
and brought the truth to light.

368
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:21,380
Thanks to that,

369
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:24,180
Shaozhong was later released

370
00:19:24,620 --> 00:19:26,060
by Mr. Yang.

371
00:19:27,380 --> 00:19:29,940
Wu, however, was penalized

372
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:31,700
with a six-month salary deduction.

373
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:32,940
Resentful,

374
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:35,140
he fled with a sum of money.

375
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:40,140
And just like that, Erniu's fate

376
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:43,420
was rewritten.

377
00:19:51,260 --> 00:19:53,340
I should board the ship now.

378
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:56,620
What are your plans moving forward?

379
00:19:57,420 --> 00:19:58,580
None, really.

380
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:03,020
After years of being entangled
in business power plays,

381
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:04,740
I'm truly exhausted.

382
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:08,660
Coming home feels like
the right moment to breathe.

383
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:12,700
Miracle Pill was saved,

384
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:15,580
but it cost you your job.

385
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:17,500
I'm truly sorry.

386
00:20:18,820 --> 00:20:20,380
You don't need to feel guilty.

387
00:20:20,660 --> 00:20:24,500
Honestly, I'd long planned
to leave Xia Yuan.

388
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:26,340
It's just

389
00:20:27,540 --> 00:20:29,940
I couldn't bring myself
to break the loyalty I felt,

390
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:31,580
or the respect I owed him as a mentor.

391
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:33,860
And of course,

392
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,820
I wasn't quite ready
to give up the paycheck.

393
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:39,140
It wasn't until that moment in court

394
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:42,220
that I finally made up my mind.

395
00:20:43,420 --> 00:20:44,420
Why was that?

396
00:20:45,540 --> 00:20:47,620
Miss Chu, as you know,

397
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,980
the Japanese are now

398
00:20:50,380 --> 00:20:52,460
shareholders in Shouyuan Apothecary.

399
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:55,660
If the Miracle Pill formula

400
00:20:55,660 --> 00:20:57,940
ends up in Shouyuan's hands,

401
00:20:58,140 --> 00:20:59,740
it would inevitably

402
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:00,940
fall into theirs as well.

403
00:21:02,020 --> 00:21:04,540
I may be an ordinary man,

404
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:08,220
but when it comes
to national interest and justice,

405
00:21:08,620 --> 00:21:11,140
I stand firm.

406
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:14,580
Mr. Gao,

407
00:21:15,940 --> 00:21:16,860
you have my deepest respect.

408
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:18,980
Please don't.

409
00:21:22,540 --> 00:21:25,460
Whenever you're ready to return,

410
00:21:26,260 --> 00:21:27,540
you'll always have a place

411
00:21:28,580 --> 00:21:30,100
at Chichun Apothecary.

412
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,300
Miss...

413
00:21:39,940 --> 00:21:40,940
Ms. Chu.

414
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:44,700
We shall meet again.

415
00:21:46,420 --> 00:21:47,060
Farewell.

416
00:22:07,020 --> 00:22:07,580
Here's your wonton.

417
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:08,420
Thank you.

418
00:22:13,620 --> 00:22:14,940
She always goes on Wednesday evenings

419
00:22:14,940 --> 00:22:16,500
to the stall by Kongjia Longtang

420
00:22:16,580 --> 00:22:17,380
to eat a bowl of wontons.

421
00:22:20,020 --> 00:22:20,780
By herself?

422
00:22:21,220 --> 00:22:21,820
Yes.

423
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:23,140
I checked it out.

424
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:24,580
That intersection is quiet at night,

425
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:25,860
making it easy to make a move.

426
00:22:31,940 --> 00:22:35,260
Mr. Xia, things have been sensitive.

427
00:22:37,060 --> 00:22:37,780
Is that so?

428
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:40,780
Two days ago, Chiang Kai-shek

429
00:22:40,780 --> 00:22:43,100
published an article

430
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:45,340
in the Japanese magazine
Economic Exchange.

431
00:22:46,180 --> 00:22:47,660
In it, he wrote:

432
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:51,780
"China's concessions
and compromises to Japan

433
00:22:51,940 --> 00:22:53,700
do have certain limits."

434
00:22:55,300 --> 00:22:56,100
Furthermore,

435
00:22:56,260 --> 00:22:58,460
he instructed the Ambassador
to Japan, Chiang Tso-pin,

436
00:22:58,780 --> 00:23:01,340
to inform our government

437
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:03,900
that should the Chinese government

438
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:06,620
be pushed beyond endurance,

439
00:23:07,100 --> 00:23:08,940
it will resist the aggressors

440
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:10,980
at all costs.

441
00:23:16,180 --> 00:23:17,460
Didn't he use to take

442
00:23:17,460 --> 00:23:19,100
a strictly non-confrontational approach?

443
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:23,980
But recently,

444
00:23:23,980 --> 00:23:25,660
in politics, military affairs,

445
00:23:26,100 --> 00:23:28,380
national defense, diplomacy, and beyond,

446
00:23:28,380 --> 00:23:29,980
he's been quietly maneuvering.

447
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:33,100
It seems his stance has shifted.

448
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:39,140
Is he really preparing for war?

449
00:23:41,340 --> 00:23:42,060
I doubt it.

450
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:44,980
But given how things are now,

451
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:46,940
he might not have a choice.

452
00:23:47,980 --> 00:23:48,860
I believe

453
00:23:49,260 --> 00:23:50,740
the war between China and Japan

454
00:23:51,260 --> 00:23:52,700
is inevitable.

455
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:55,780
You must hurry

456
00:23:55,780 --> 00:23:57,500
and secure what we want

457
00:23:58,060 --> 00:23:59,660
before war breaks out.

458
00:24:04,940 --> 00:24:05,580
Alright.

459
00:24:07,620 --> 00:24:08,420
I'll make the arrangements.

460
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:13,660
That's the situation with Marketing.

461
00:24:15,420 --> 00:24:16,220
What about your side?

462
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:18,380
It's about the new factory site.

463
00:24:18,820 --> 00:24:20,220
We had a good plot of land all set,

464
00:24:20,220 --> 00:24:21,420
and we were just about to sign

465
00:24:21,860 --> 00:24:23,980
when the owner suddenly pulled out.

466
00:24:24,380 --> 00:24:25,540
I asked around,

467
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:28,820
and it turns out they got threatened
by some officials.

468
00:24:29,780 --> 00:24:30,660
Ma Juncai's guys?

469
00:24:31,220 --> 00:24:31,900
Probably.

470
00:24:38,860 --> 00:24:40,900
Why not look elsewhere?

471
00:24:41,780 --> 00:24:42,580
I think

472
00:24:42,820 --> 00:24:44,820
Southwest China seems promising.

473
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:47,780
We don't have to stay tied
to Shanghai or Nanjing.

474
00:24:48,340 --> 00:24:49,140
I'll get on it right away.

475
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:50,380
Okay.

476
00:24:51,860 --> 00:24:53,420
Great work today, everyone.

477
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:54,700
Let's call it a day.

478
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:56,020
Go home and get some rest.

479
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:57,540
Shaohua,

480
00:24:57,940 --> 00:24:59,220
heading straight home later?

481
00:24:59,420 --> 00:25:01,900
I'm craving a bowl of wontons
before I go.

482
00:25:02,820 --> 00:25:03,740
I'll come with you.

483
00:25:05,420 --> 00:25:06,900
Don't you usually skip supper

484
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:07,980
to keep your figure?

485
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:10,340
I just felt like having some today.

486
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:12,420
You usually go alone,

487
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:13,340
but tonight, I'm joining you.

488
00:25:13,740 --> 00:25:14,540
Alright.

489
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:17,140
Cheng Hui, you coming?

490
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:18,780
I need to head to the factory later.

491
00:25:18,780 --> 00:25:19,540
I'll pass.

492
00:25:19,540 --> 00:25:20,220
You two go ahead.

493
00:25:20,220 --> 00:25:21,660
Alright, we're off.

494
00:25:22,540 --> 00:25:23,300
Oh, and Shaohua,

495
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:24,540
watch yourself, alright?

496
00:25:24,700 --> 00:25:25,100
Okay.

497
00:25:25,100 --> 00:25:26,220
Don't worry, I'm here.

498
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:33,420
It's right there.

499
00:25:35,380 --> 00:25:36,460
Pretty packed today.

500
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:41,460
Go take a seat.

501
00:25:43,260 --> 00:25:43,940
Excuse me,

502
00:25:44,580 --> 00:25:45,620
two bowls of wontons.

503
00:25:45,620 --> 00:25:46,340
Alright.

504
00:25:58,140 --> 00:25:59,180
Is something wrong?

505
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:03,260
Feels like someone's been
keeping an eye on me.

506
00:26:05,580 --> 00:26:07,020
Could it be Ma Juncai's guys?

507
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:09,380
Hard to say.

508
00:26:10,060 --> 00:26:10,660
Thank you.

509
00:26:30,060 --> 00:26:31,100
Did they send

510
00:26:31,780 --> 00:26:32,900
those three bullets?

511
00:26:34,540 --> 00:26:35,620
Those guys

512
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:38,940
love using scare tactics.

513
00:26:41,020 --> 00:26:44,540
I heard Yang Xingfo and Shi Liangcai

514
00:26:44,820 --> 00:26:45,980
were both killed by them.

515
00:26:48,260 --> 00:26:48,980
Shaohua,

516
00:26:49,580 --> 00:26:50,940
I'm afraid they'll lay a hand on you.

517
00:26:55,380 --> 00:26:56,700
Thank you.

518
00:26:59,180 --> 00:26:59,980
Let's finish up quickly

519
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:01,340
and get going.

520
00:27:02,340 --> 00:27:03,620
Be extra careful these days

521
00:27:03,980 --> 00:27:05,020
and try not to go out alone.

522
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:07,700
I'll go add some cilantro.

523
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:08,220
Okay.

524
00:27:09,580 --> 00:27:11,820
Sir, I'd like more cilantro.

525
00:27:12,300 --> 00:27:13,460
Alright, help yourself.

526
00:27:13,460 --> 00:27:14,020
Okay.

527
00:27:23,620 --> 00:27:24,500
Shaohua, watch out!

528
00:27:33,300 --> 00:27:33,900
Erniu!

529
00:27:36,620 --> 00:27:37,220
Erniu!

530
00:27:37,500 --> 00:27:38,100
Erniu!

531
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:39,180
Erniu!

532
00:27:40,020 --> 00:27:40,740
Erniu!

533
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:41,820
Erniu!

534
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:44,580
Hurry! Get a ride!

535
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:45,980
Okay.

536
00:27:47,540 --> 00:27:49,180
Erniu, hang in there.

537
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:50,260
Shaohua,

538
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:53,020
I've actually been shot.

539
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:54,740
It hurts so much.

540
00:27:55,260 --> 00:27:56,780
I'm taking you to the hospital.

541
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:57,660
Ouch.

542
00:27:57,820 --> 00:27:58,660
Hang in there.

543
00:27:58,660 --> 00:28:00,380
[Operating Room]

544
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:07,460
Doctor.

545
00:28:07,940 --> 00:28:09,780
Good thing it missed anything vital.

546
00:28:10,020 --> 00:28:10,660
Don't worry.

547
00:28:48,780 --> 00:28:49,420
You're awake.

548
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:56,220
Where am I?

549
00:28:57,260 --> 00:28:57,980
The hospital.

550
00:28:58,940 --> 00:29:01,500
The doctor just operated on you.

551
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:03,260
The bullet has been removed.

552
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:06,500
I can't believe they actually fired.

553
00:29:09,900 --> 00:29:11,100
Thankfully, you're alright.

554
00:29:12,300 --> 00:29:15,340
The doctor said you lost a lot of blood

555
00:29:15,940 --> 00:29:17,620
and need proper rest.

556
00:29:22,220 --> 00:29:23,500
Are you alright?

557
00:29:24,900 --> 00:29:25,740
I'm fine.

558
00:29:28,020 --> 00:29:29,060
But you almost...

559
00:29:33,740 --> 00:29:34,740
You knew

560
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:36,580
they were going to kill me.

561
00:29:37,660 --> 00:29:38,900
Why did you run toward them?

562
00:29:38,900 --> 00:29:39,820
Why didn't you dodge?

563
00:29:41,620 --> 00:29:43,060
If it were you,

564
00:29:45,340 --> 00:29:46,940
you'd have done the same,

565
00:29:47,660 --> 00:29:48,460
wouldn't you?

566
00:29:49,700 --> 00:29:50,620
I don't know.

567
00:29:52,580 --> 00:29:54,020
I'm not as brave as you.

568
00:29:56,620 --> 00:29:57,980
I'm not brave.

569
00:30:00,140 --> 00:30:01,300
I just

570
00:30:03,700 --> 00:30:04,860
don't want to lose you.

571
00:30:14,820 --> 00:30:15,580
Erniu.

572
00:30:16,700 --> 00:30:17,460
Thank you.

573
00:30:19,100 --> 00:30:20,500
We don't do formalities,

574
